      "community": "Jain Resource Recycling Ltd : A metal recycling compounder in the making",
      "timestamp": "2026-05-18T16:04:10.270Z",
      "text": "Across the industry, processing margins have faced immense pressure, forcing companies to rely purely on premium products or volume expansions rather than high margins per ton. The topline is high because of the high-volume, lower-margin product mix. They are currently pushing heavy volumes of basic copper ingots to capture market share and feed their massive ongoing capex, sacrificing near-term margins for topline scaling. This margin dip is likely in a transitional phase because input scrap costs rose faster than selling prices. The margin story will likely only structurally turn around once…",
      "url": "https://forum.valuepickr.com/t/jain-resource-recycling-ltd-a-metal-recycling-compounder-in-the-making/217970/20",
      "sentiment": "bearish",
      "likes": 2,
      "comments": 1
    },
    {
